review_data.content: Great place with a lovely atmosphere, good food, and friendly/accommodating staff. I really feel the staff go above and beyond here to give you the best service possible.
Used to be a good place. Been today … food not fresh, waters plainly rude, got only half order,  manager disinterested … I think we will not be returning any time soon …

The place looked good from outside but it was the worst Sushi ever I had...Generally it tasted like nothing. Rice was too hard(It must be very old). Also,  Salmon and Tuna were not fresh at all. I've also ordered Karage(Japanise chicken) and the pieces were very small like nuggets and served with somehow Basmati rice lol. it was very disappointing. The server can't speak 'hochdeutsch'.
Super nice place and very kind staff. The food is good and the restaurant looks good. The prices are a bit higher than usual but good food just costs a bit more. :)

One of the best meals I’ve had in switzerland as a vegetarian. Fantastic options for vegans and vegetarians. Food is amazing and so is the srtvice and decor. Try the soup bowls and sushi. Out of this world. Especially the black rice with tofu skin sushi. The spring rolls had absorbed too much oil so they were greasy but yum! Pictured- noodle soup bowl vegetarian, vegetarian sushi , salted edamame, shrimp dumpling, spring roll, fish sushi, miso soup. All of them excellent.

Quite frankly I don't understand the hype nor the five stars.
I found the place to be quite nice and welcoming, but can't say the same for the staff. The food was overpriced for what it was: a mediocre sushi restaurant.
You can find much much better quality of sushi and ingredients overall elsewhere.
The sushi was dry and tasteless as it was so poor of seafood or other condiments and the noodles, or should I say common spaghetti, were salty and not what I expect of a Japanese dish.
Not sure I'll be back for a second time even though I really wanted to try the desserts.

This is my favorite restaurant! I love it so much. I come to this restaurant a lot and every year on my birthday.
I always bring my friends here and they enjoy it just as much as I do.
The food is just excellent. And the people there are super friendly. I always get the California Rolls. Everyone must try these.

Considering the Switzerland does not have access to the sea and therefore will never have the same quality fish as you would get in other place, Negishi Sushi is a good place to get sushi. Resonable prices and very friendly staff.
Great place for Sushi. We usally order here once a week. Sushi has a great quality and is always fresh. Friendly stuff an nice interior!
Beautiful Sushi and nice restaurant, easy to get to with public transport
Nice sushi, but the waitress’s service is not so good.

Order online to pick up at the store.
Didn't pay attention when i picked up the food. When i got home I realized and they "forgot" about 20% worth of food from the order.
We order frequently from this nice restaurant and food is always very tasty and fresh!
Good selection of sushi's. Good ramen
exceptionally good - friendly staff.

Very nice built place with a great selection of sushis, the soups are also nice and the dumplings well made, the staff is big and most friendly, clean and interesting room with a good deal of sitting arrangements, if it where a tiny bit less expensive then it would get 5 stars, but overall nice and a good experience
Amazing food and place. Atmosphere in the restaurant is quite chill and relaxing.
Ordered sushi delivery, quick and accurate, however we were not impressed with the food, for us not exceptional but only average.

The quality of the sushi from this establishment has steadily declined over the last year. The fish is no longer sliced along the natural lines, creating a very stringy texture (most visible in the tuna, which feels very "chewy"). The rice sometimes does not stick properly and the rolls fall apart as you try to eat them. Add to that recurrent delivery issues and this is simply not worth the price they are charging
Not traditional Japaness resturant. If you want to eat the fusion Japaness food, this resturant is not bad choice.
Nice restaurant, staff are friendly. Food is pretty poor. We had the noodle soups and they were a joke.

So Good Sushi and super Service
Until very soon
Always fresh food is prepared on time with all the instructions followed. Thank you.

Tried a poke bowl for a whopping 26 francs, and very disappointed. Mushy luke warm noodles topped with no sauce or seasoning, salmon chopped in little cubes and not the slices as shown in the menu. Just plain toppings in conservative portions, nothing done to give this expensive bowl any special taste. The cooks here have to realize that today's Swiss customers have traveled and know the quality that you get in places like Singapore and London. Even Germany has figured this out. I will not eat again at this overpriced chain.

A bit average.
Sushi was OK, some other dishes less so.

Great food, but way to overpriced. You pay 90.- for something that barely fills you up. Of course Sushi is expensive everywhere in Switzerland but it‘s just a rip-off at some point. Also the seating is a bit awkward the staff is okay.
very good food and the staff is always really friendly. 10/10

Have ordered here multiple times now and everytime they have either managed to not give me my complete order or given me the wrong order completely! They couldn't help when I called the hotline to complain.

Got a call from the the following day to apologise and give me a voucher for the next time I order.

Thank you very much Tobias.

Great selection and helpful staff. The package deals for 2+ people are great and there is an option for self service take away. It is hit or miss leaving comments on the order when placing it online, so make sure to double check your order when you pick it up if you have any special preferences
I havent ate yet, lets see if i win :D

Food is excellent..location superb..service could definitely be worked upon and taken many notches higher! Not our first time - hence the critical observation. And since the family are avid sushi lovers, are focus up until now entirely been the quality of the food👍🏼

Located in the city center of Zug close to a shopping mall. Offers a number of outside seats. Kind of modern style, but without a catchy atmosphere. Menu looks interesting and we had the soup, some Sushi variations and fried Edamame beans and sweet potato. All good, but not really delivering to the interesting menu. Especially the Sushi tasted prepared for the day and overall not much exciting. Service was friendly, but average and took pretty long.
It is average in my opinion. Conveniently located if you’re shopping at Metalli.
Nice ambiance, good quality food, nice presentation.
The food is excellent but the staff is not really friendly and doesn‘t pay attention at all to their customers….

for Sushi in Switzerland (which simply never achieves the level of quality of the US coastal cities like NYC, Boston or San Francisco) the Sushi here is pretty goid and the service is extremely friendly. We have come here now for over five years and never had a bad experience.
Great food, friendly staff

Pros:
Welcoming place, nice staff, perfect location

Cons:
The food is literally not bad but just doesn’t taste authentic, and seems overpriced for the quality, especially given the situation there are better sushi choices in zug.

Looking forward to improvement!
Top quality sushi with a large menu and many variations. The rice is excellent. The fish fresh. A bit too expensive.

Friendly staff but sushi way too big and not presented the way it is shown on the menu. And quality was also not the best. I suspect some of the roles have been made before because the rice was dry. Not really my favorite sushi place anymore after such an experience. Was way better in the past. Shame.

Altough the sushi is very good and if reasonable price. The service was terrible. The waiter seemed arrogant and made us feel uncomfortable being there. No one greeted us when we arrived despite us, until we found the table I'd reserved ourselves. And after waiting 15' for the bill we had to get up and request it and the front. It was clear to see that older guests were being treated better than us. Over all I wouldn't recommend for anyone under 30
The quality of the food is just bad. The service is just as bad. But you cant blame the waiters because the manager is not nice. They are in the wrong business.

Awesome sushi place - excellent selection of  platters as well as individual rolls and sashimi. All the staples present as well as some rather unusual items. One gripe though - beer only in 33ml measures and no draft. Prices are about average for Switzerland, but on the high side for the UK.
New menu is quite interesting. Don't take the healthy rolls though, they're rather boring and mine had fishbones in them. Riesling is good.

Average - the best thing they offer for me is the Mito's Poke. Everything else is not worth trying if you stay in Zug. Location is good and interior is nice. The Sushi is really just below average with a very strange selection of rolls. Eg. No normal Tuna rolls just spicy or mousse. Try Kaiten or Aki instead. Much higher quality Sushi.

The service is so-so and the sushi is so-so-so...
We had a sushi platter, dim sum, chicken noodle soup etc, and it looked interesting but it all tasted the same... and like only rice. The Crispy Prawn California Rolls were... well, not crispy at all - the tempura was chewy as if its been on the shelf all day and the prawns were more like miniature shrimps. Won’t go back for sushi... maybe for the noodle soup. But if you’re at Metalli and you want a quick bite, it could be good for that.

We went there right after they opened and didn't think the sushi was that good, but we've since then gone back several times and they've clearly improved. This is now very good sushi, the service is quite good, and the ambiance (if not very Japanese style) is really nice.

We also order online delivery from them quite often and it's the same great quality. They do make a small mistake every so often on the order.
Delicious sushi and homemade ice tea! Cool to hang out on the terasse on a sunny day. Two types of edamame, i recommend the classic one. The other with sweet potatoes is a bit too heavy.

This Sushi and Japaneese food restaurant is the best! The price + quality compared, makes it the best place to eat Sushi in Zug.
They have a big variation of Sushi, vegetables and other asian food. They also have Vegetarian sushi. A must-to-visit restaurant in Zug. A big like from me.

Not good sushi. The location and ambience is great but sushi is bad. The rice used is not fresh. And that makes the sushi hard. Plus when we went the waiter forgot to bring one of our orders and then was telling us that he did and we forgot that we ate.

Cozy and classy Japan restaurant.  Very impressive meals and drinks menu for any types of cousins lovers.  Has a self-service deck,  cards check-out s. Quite easy-to-reach location.  Recommended for quick and long-standing visits.

Incredibly humiliating experience and poor service. After being seated and having waited for menu for at least 15min, restaurant manager named Lukas came to my table and started shouting because I was sitting at a reserved table. When I followed him and politely asked to be seated inside and getting menu after a long wait he pointed at the door and very loud in front of entire restaurant told me that I should leave if there is anything I don’t like. The manager was really aggressive and unpleasant without any reason. I would like to be informed what measures will be taken in this specific situation and also to prevent similar customer treatment in future. Overall, I do not recommend this restaurant for women and foreigners
Modern and stylish restaurant with a great sushi selection

We love this sushi restaurant, we're always going as a group of five and grabbing one of three booths with the sushi-belt going by. The sushi selection is fresh, inventive, and always has something for everyone. It has become our sushi-of-choice go to place.

The online reservation system kicks ass to boot!
Great shrimp 🍤 sushi! Our favorite

An expensive, typical, modernist sushi restaurant franchise.

Nice atmosphere, very clean inside and modern. Staff is most polite and they have at least one Japanese person working there to add some authenticity.

Their ramen = water + noodles (zero flavor in broth) + 25 CHF… Recommend going to Zurich (ie Ramen Ya, Miki Ramen, Ikoo Ramen) for a better experience for this particular cuisine.

Very good quality desserts, albeit pricey. Otherwise- a pleasant experience…

Gift wrapped in an ultra modern design of a sparse production facility, the Negishi is a trendy and vibrant Mecca of hand crafted sushi and cool music. Perfect for a large groups on the giant slabs of tables and bench or if you prefer the more intimate elegance of private seating, the ambiance is both futuristic and perfectionism. I loved the wasabi, hand made and one of the best in the world. The giant square windows and over sized light clusters, the depth of black and the crafted leather chairs. Eventing is as they wear of their uniforms...same, same just different...the menu is awesome in selection and the selection of sushi I tried included a very rare and difficult to acquire kimchi. Whether you want a late night rendezvous or the start of a party night with friends at the Negishi you simply do it all in style.
Very good sushi, nice ambience. Friendly waiters.
One of the best place to take delicious sushis in Zug! I recommend to take the rolls of sushis with Harumaki :)

We've been there so many times during the last two years. The selection and quality has improved substantially and and is not that expensive. They also have Hitachino beers, a Japanese brewery. Placed in a convenient spot just in the middle of the shopping area. Parking provided by the Metalli shopping mall.

If you happen to be there during summer, be sure to take one of their fruity wine based drinks!

No-one would travel to Zug for some Sushi. Once you accept that, the Negishi is a pretty good place. The best Sushi restaurant in Zug, and surprisingly good for such a small town. Clean, a bit sterile, but comfortably spacious and less expensive than you probably expect.

Terrible!! Period! Terrible! As I'm still seating here wondering how unfortunate we were for choosing to eat here instead of our usual Aki just down the street. Cold sushi... Migros sushi actually tastes better. Nice decor... But not worth it! Don't go here! Please don't!

Sushi is not to be recommended, rise is not good, rolls are not holding good and does not look good for money. But worst is service, rude, unprofessional. Picking up packed Sushi in Migros or Coop may give you more pleasure then eating in Negishi.
Great hours and location, sushi is well presented but average at best

Let down by the quality of service.

The food is fine and reasonably priced like any Negishi,  but you'll be lucky if you get what you order. If you complain, don't expect them to take any notice.
Overpriced for subpar quality food and small portions.
great food and beautiful presentation
If you are looking for high quality sushi in the heart of Zug, then this is the place to go. Only downside: relatively high prices. Overall high value for money.

A very cool place to get some tasty sushi! Make sure you reserve a table just in case! A wider range of sashimi would be great!

5 stars becauae Alex was an amazing and outstanding waitress. Food was of the same goof quality as usual.

Great food and atmosphere

Delicious sushi, beautiful platters. Very expensive, but I think it's just the prices for Zug.
Great food and nice drinks, this is my favourite sushi place in Zug
Asian fast-food popular during lunch time. Simple dishes, nothing fancy. Average pricing. It is OK.
Good food, nice employees especially the ukrainian lady. Very professional and great host.

Great sushi at the center of Zug in Metalli, with a vibrant atmosphere.
